<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>sl0wguy</title><link>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/</link><description>Recent content on sl0wguy</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 03 Aug 2019 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://leopoldabgn.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Introduction</title><link>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/posts/what-is-hugo/</link><pubDate>Sat, 03 Aug 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/posts/what-is-hugo/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Hugo is an open-source project and lives by the work of its contributors. There are plenty of open issues, and we need your help to make Hugo even more awesome. You don&amp;rsquo;t need to be a Go guru to contribute to the project&amp;rsquo;s development.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>What is Hugo</title><link>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/posts/introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jul 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/posts/introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Hugo is a fast and modern static site generator written in Go, and designed to make website creation fun again.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title/><link>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/about/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://leopoldabgn.github.io/about/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="about-me"&gt;About Me&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;Holding a &lt;strong&gt;Master’s degree in Cybersecurity&lt;/strong&gt; from Sorbonne Université, I am a certified &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://credentials.offsec.com/5ef03d93-c647-4231-8bb0-ab8f8d2106bb#acc.37f694ks" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;OSCP+&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; professional with a focused background in penetration testing and programming. Beyond hands-on training on platforms like &lt;a href="https://ap